# System mail aliases (local Postfix -> mailcow relay)
# Cron and other system services send mail to "root", which gets expanded
# to root@example.com via myorigin. Since example.com is not
# in mydestination, /etc/aliases does NOT apply -- virtual_alias_maps is
# needed to rewrite the recipient before relaying to mailcow.
root@example.com		admin@example.com
